  "text": "<html>\r\n    <head>\r\n    <style>\r\n        .unselectable {\r\n          -webkit-user-select: none;\r\n          -webkit-touch-callout: none;\r\n          -moz-user-select: none;\r\n          -ms-user-select: none;\r\n          user-select: none;\r\n        }\r\n      <\/style>\r\n      <\/head>\r\n\r\n<body class=\"unselectable\">\r\n \r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">CONSTITUTION<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Features of a federal constitution<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">written and rigid<\/span><\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Bicameral legislature&nbsp;<\/span><\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Supremacy of constitution&nbsp;<\/span><\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Supreme Court&nbsp;<\/span><\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Division of power&nbsp;<\/span><\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Rigorous amendment&nbsp;<\/span><\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:28.52pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:7.48pt; font-family:serif; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Preamble&nbsp;<\/span><\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A constitutional preamble is a short introductory statement.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The introductory part always portrays the essence of the constitution.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Constitutional Development in Nigeria<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Clifford Constitution, 1922<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Richard Constitution, 1946<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Macpherson Constitution, 1951<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Lyttleton Constitution, 1954&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">1957\/58 was the Constitutional Conference<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Independence Constitution, 1960<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The Republican Constitution, 1963<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The 1979 Constitution<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The 1989 Constitution<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The 1999 Constitution<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Lyttleton constitution&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">actually established the true federalism. Which classified government power into three, namely the exclusive, the concurrent and the residual powers.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Richards Constitution&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">divided the country into three regions and thus laid the foundation for federalism in Nigeria<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">In the 1963 Constitution, the president is ceremonial and he exercised nominal powers. While Prime minister and his cabinet performed the Executive functions and exercised executive powers.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The Governor&#39;s office as the representative of the queen was abolished in 1963 by the republican Constitution.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Crisis in the National Council of Nigeria and Cameroon (NCNC) led to the breakdown of the Macpherson Constitution of 1951.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The emergence of Republican Constitution of 1963 made the Supreme Court become the highest Court of Appeal in Nigeria. Before 1963 the judicial committee for the privy council was the highest court of appeal.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">In the 1979 constitution of Nigeria residual power were vested in the state government. Exclusive powers were for the federal government only and concurrent powers were for the federal and regional state governments.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A major feature which differentiated the 1963 and 1979 constitutions was that in 1963 constitution ministers were appointed from the National Assembly.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A written constitution must contain a ___.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. dialogue, B. discourse, C. preamble, D. summary<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C (2005\/2006, no 4).<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Preamble&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">12. The constitution that gave the regions more autonomy was<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. Clifford&#39;s Constitution 1922<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">B. Richard&#39;s Constitution 1946<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. Macpherson Constitution 1951<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D. Lyttleton Constitution 1954<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Macpherson Constitution 1951<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Macpherson Constitution 1951, constitution granted more powers to the regional Houses of Assembly. The constitution allowed them to make laws and advice on most matters concerning their own people.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The constitution that gave the regions more autonomy was<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. Clifford&#39;s Constitution 1922. B. Richard&#39;s Constitution 1946<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. Macpherson Constitution 1951. D. Lyttleton Constitution 1954<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C (2007\/2008, no 12).<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Macpherson Constitution 1951<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Macpherson Constitution 1951, constitution granted more powers to the regional Houses of Assembly. The constitution allowed them to make laws and advice on most matters concerning their own people.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">16. A federal constitution is usually___.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. flexible, B. unwritten, C. written and flexible, D. written and rigid<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D (2018\/2019, no 16)<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n \r\n<\/body>\r\n\r\n<\/html>",
  "chapIndex": "CONSTITUTION"
}